   Raspberry Pi Toolchain used by Marshmallow Game Engine (@marshmallow_h)
==============================================================================

How to use
----------

You will need to source the environment file (currently only works with sh and bash).

    $ source ./env

This will add populate the following environment variables used by 'marshmallow_h'.

    RPITOOLCHAIN_HOST
    RPITOOLCHAIN_TARGET
    RPITOOLCHAIN
    RPIFIRMWARE

Now, go to your local 'marshmallow_h' cloned repository, go into the build
directory and run the following command:

    $ cmake -DCMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE=../cmake/Toolchain-raspberrypi.cmake ..

Now cross your fingers and run 'make'.

